33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=bryek>Bryek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/17/01 11:01:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> If they want to wipe our wizard quad kiting all they have to do is make our snares single target.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwalaskin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Walaskin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/17/01 11:03:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: About Shackles resists....and Verant's solo policy</span><hr size=1> maybe they are going by a different angle and saying if we aren't good in grps they will make us better at soloing <p><img src= http://freepages.ugo.com/walaskin/files/walaskin.jpg> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=nyargle>Nyargle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/17/01 11:13:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: About Shackles resists....and Verant's solo policy</span><hr size=1> Frankly, I like our soloing power, and hope our quadkiting doesn't get nerfed.  There are plenty of places in Norrath where soloing is next to impossible for a wizard, so that should be taken into account.<br><br>Once we wizards are more valuable in a group situation, we won't have to become so good at soloing any more because we will be wanted in groups.  The only reason we're so good at quad-kiting is because we've honed our skills to do that, since nobody wanted to add us to their group anyways.  Sure, we've been given the tools for high powered soloing, but often learning to use these tools (aoe snare, aoe nukes) is as important as the tools themselves. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucalinot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Calinot</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/17/01 12:57:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: About Shackles resists....and Verant's solo policy</span><hr size=1> They reduced the resist check on Atol's Spectral Shackles because a level 51 spell shouldn't have the same resist check as a level 29 spell (Bonds of Force). They don't want us to be better solo which is why the resist check is now Magic+15 as opposed to Magic+0 which it should be. 10 points isn't enough to make that big of a diffrence but enough to call it an upgrade, I'm surprised we got 10 points instead of just 1. <p>I've been cursed by god to wander the earth in an endless quest to conquer man.Light a man a fire, and he will be warm for a day.Light a man on fire, and he will bewarm for the rest of his life. </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3333